#. Help manual
#: activities/checkers/ActivityInfo.qml:23
msgctxt "ActivityInfo|"
msgid ""
"Checkers is played by two opponents, on opposite sides of the gameboard. One "
"player has the dark pieces; the other has the light pieces. Players "
"alternate turns. A player may not move an opponent's piece. A move consists "
"of moving a piece diagonally to an adjacent unoccupied square. If the "
"adjacent square contains an opponent's piece, and the square immediately "
"beyond it is vacant, the piece may be captured (and removed from the game) "
"by jumping over it.\n"
"Only the dark squares of the checkered board are used. A piece may move only "
"diagonally into an unoccupied square. Capturing is mandatory. The player "
"without pieces remaining, or who cannot move due to being blocked, loses the "
"game.\n"
"When a man reaches the crownhead or kings row (the farthest row forward), it "
"becomes a king, and is marked by placing an additional piece on top of the "
"first man, and acquires additional powers including the ability to move "
"backwards. If there is a piece in a diagonal that a king can capture, he can "
"move any distance along the diagonal, and may capture an opposing man any "
"distance away by jumping to any of the unoccupied squares immediately beyond "
"it."
msgstr ""
"Dama oyunu lΡüvh…ônin …ôks t…ôr…ôfl…ôrind…ô oturan iki oyunΟßu arasΡ±nda oynanΡ±r. Bir "
"oyunΟßu qara da≈ülarla, dig…ôr oyunΟßu is…ô aΡü da≈ülarla oynayΡ±r. OyunΟßular nΟΕvb…ô "
"il…ô oynayΡ±rlar. OyunΟßu r…ôqibin da≈ülarΡ± il…ô oynaya bilm…ôz. Gedi≈ü, bir dama "
"da≈üΡ±nΡ±n biti≈üik bo≈ü kvadrata Οßarpaz ≈ü…ôkild…ô kΟΕΟßΟΦrΟΦlm…ôsind…ôn ibar…ôtdir. "
"Biti≈üik kvadratda r…ôqibin da≈üΡ± varsa v…ô ondan sonrakΡ± kvadrat bo≈üdursa, "
"ΟΦz…ôrind…ôn atlayaraq r…ôqibin da≈üΡ± alΡ±na (v…ô ya oyundan ΟßΡ±xarΡ±la) bil…ôr.\n"
"Dama taxtasΡ±nΡ±n yalnΡ±z qara damalarΡ±ndan istifad…ô olunur. Bir dama da≈üΡ± "
"yalnΡ±z Οßarpaz olaraq dog…ôr damaya doΡüru gedi≈ü ed…ô bil…ôr. H…ôr hansΡ± bir "
"damanΡ±n tutlmasΡ± m…ôcburidir. ArtΡ±q da≈ülarΡ± qalmayan v…ô a bΟΦtΟΦn gedi≈ül…ôri "
"baΡülandΡ±ΡüΡ± ΟΦΟßΟΦn h…ôr…ôk…ôt ed…ô bilm…ôy…ôn oyunΟßu oyunu uduzur.\n"
"Τèg…ôr oyunΟßu r…ôqibin sonuncu c…ôrg…ôsin…ô Οßatarsa, onun bu da≈üΡ± \"Damaya\" "
"Οßevrilir. Bunun ΟΦΟßΟΦn o iki da≈üΡ± ΟΦst-ΟΦst…ô qoyur. Damaya Οßevrilmi≈ü da≈ü oyun "
"x…ôtti ΟΦzr…ô ist…ônil…ôn istiqam…ôtd…ô (h…ôm ir…ôli, h…ôm d…ô geri) v…ô addΡ±mla h…ôr…ôk…ôt "
"ed…ô bilir. Ancaq dama r…ôqib da≈üΡ±nΡ±n ΟΦz…ôrind…ôn atΡ±ldΡ±qda o mΟΦtl…ôq h…ômin da≈üΡ±n "
"arxasΡ±nda dayanmalΡ±dΡ±r. Bi DamanΡ±n …ôl…ô keΟßir…ô bil…ôc…ôyi diaqonalda bir r…ôqib "
"da≈üΡ± varsa, h…ômin diaqnalda ist…ônil…ôn m…ôsaf…ôni q…ôt ed…ôr…ôk r…ôqib da≈üΡ±nΡ±n "
"arxasΡ±na keΟßm…ôkl…ô onu oyundan ΟßΡ±xara bil…ôr."

