msgstr "Verilmi≈ü abid…ônin yerl…ô≈üdiyi yer…ô vurun."

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board6.qml:17
#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board6.qml:20
msgctxt "board6|"
msgid "Great Pyramid of Giza"
msgstr "Xeops ehramlarΡ±"

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board6.qml:18
msgctxt "board6|"
msgid ""
"The Great Pyramid of Giza is also known as the Pyramid of Khufu or the "
"Pyramid of Cheops. It is considered to be the oldest of all the Seven "
"Wonders of the Ancient World. It is also the largest of all the three "
"pyramids in Giza. It is situated in the Giza Necropolis, in Egypt. The "
"initial construction has been started by Egyptian Pharaoh Khufu, then it was "
"continued by his son Khafre and finally completed by Menkaure. It took "
"almost 20 years to build the pyramid and approximately 2 million blocks of "
"stone have been used in the construction. The height of the pyramid is "
"approximately 139 meters making it the highest pyramid of Egypt."
msgstr ""
"Xeops ehramlarΡ± h…ômΟßinin QizanΡ±n bΟΕyΟΦk ehramlarΡ± kimi tanΡ±nΡ±r. Bu n…ôh…ông "
"Misir ehramlarΡ± DΟΦnyanΡ±n Yeddi MΟΕcΟΦz…ôl…ôrind…ôn gΟΦnΟΦmΟΦz…ô q…ôd…ôr g…ôlib Οßatan "
"yegan…ô abid…ôl…ôrdir. PiramidalarΡ±n tikintisi Misir fironu Xufu t…ôr…ôfind…ôn "
"ba≈üladΡ±lΡ±b, oΡülu Xefren t…ôr…ôfind…ôn davam etdirilib v…ô Menkuara'nΡ±n dΟΕvrΟΦnd…ô "
"ba≈üa ΟßatΡ±b. Tikinti i≈ül…ôri 20 il davam edib v…ô tikintid…ô 20 milyon da≈ü "
"bloklardan istifad…ô olunub. HΟΦndΟΦrlΟΦyΟΦ t…ôxmin…ôn 139 metrdir."

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board6.qml:28
#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board6.qml:31
msgctxt "board6|"
msgid "Bent Pyramid"
msgstr "SΡ±nmΡ±≈ü Ehram"

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board6.qml:29
msgctxt "board6|"
msgid ""
"The Bent Pyramid located at Dahshur was the second pyramid built by pharaoh "
"Sneferu. Mysteriously, this true pyramid rises from the desert at an angle "
"of 55 degrees and then suddenly changes to a more gradual angle of 43 "
"degrees. One theory holds that due to the steepness of the original angle "
"the weight to be added above the inner chambers and passageways became too "
"large, forcing the builders to adopt a shallower angle. Today, the Bent "
"Pyramid is the only pyramid in Egypt of which the outer casing of polished "
"limestone is still largely intact."
msgstr ""
"Da≈üxurda yerl…ô≈ü…ôn SΡ±nmΡ±≈ü Ehram firon Snofu t…ôr…ôfind…ôn in≈üa edil…ôn ikinci "
"ehramdΡ±r. O, yerd…ôn 55 d…ôr…ôc…ô meyillik il…ô ucalΡ±r v…ô bucaq bird…ôn t…ôdric…ôn "
"43 d…ôr…ôc…ô meyilliy…ô q…ôd…ôr azalΡ±r. Bir n…ôz…ôriyy…ôy…ô gΟΕr…ô, orijinal bucaΡüΡ±n "
"dikliyi s…ôb…ôbind…ôn daxili otaqlar v…ô keΟßid yollarΡ±nΡ±n ΟΦstΟΦn…ô …ôlav…ô edil…ôc…ôk "
"aΡüΡ±rlΡ±ΡüΡ±n Οßox bΟΕyΟΦk olmasΡ±, in≈üaatΟßΡ±larΡ± bucaΡüΡ± azaltmaΡüa m…ôcbur etmi≈üdir. "
"Bu gΟΦn SΡ±nmΡ±≈ü Ehram, cilalanmΡ±≈ü …ôh…ôngd…ôn olan ΟΕrtΟΦyΟΦ bu gΟΦn…ô q…ôd…ôr dem…ôk "
"olar ki, toxunulmamΡ±≈ü qalan yegan…ô Misir ehramΡ±dΡ±r."

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board6.qml:39
#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board6.qml:42
msgctxt "board6|"
msgid "Pyramid of Meidum"
msgstr "Meydum ehramΡ±"

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board6.qml:40
msgctxt "board6|"
msgid ""
"Five miles south of Saqqara in Egypt stands the mysterious tower-like "
"pyramid of Meidum, which today scarcely resembles a typical pyramid at all. "
"This pyramid was probably built during the reign of the 4th Dynasty pharaoh "
"Sneferu, although it is believed by some that the pyramid may have been "
"started by SneferuβÄôs predecessor, Huni. At some point during its "
"construction the steps of the pyramid were filled with limestone encasing "
"marking the first attempt by the ancient Egyptians at the construction of a "
"true pyramid."
msgstr ""
"Misirin Saqqara ≈ü…ôh…ôrind…ôn be≈ü mil c…ônubda, bu gΟΦn, piramidadan daha Οßox "
"sirli bir qalaya b…ônz…ôy…ôn Meidum ehramΡ± dayanΡ±r. Bu ehram, ehtimal ki, 4-cΟΦ "
"sΟΦlal…ô fironu Sneferunun hakimiyy…ôti dΟΕvrΟΦnd…ô tikilmi≈üdir, lakin b…ôzil…ôri "
"ehramΡ±n tikintisinin SneferuβÄônun s…ôl…ôfi Huni t…ôr…ôfind…ôn ba≈üladΡ±ldΡ±ΡüΡ±nΡ± iddia "
"edirl…ôr. ΡΑn≈üasΡ± zamanΡ± mΟΦ…ôyy…ôn vaxtlarda ehramΡ±n pill…ôl…ôri kir…ôc il…ô "
"doldurulmu≈üdur, bu da misirlil…ôrin ilk d…ôf…ô ehram tikm…ôl…ôrin…ô c…ôhd etm…ôl…ôri "
"kimi q…ôbul olunur."

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board6.qml:50
#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board6.qml:53
msgctxt "board6|"
msgid "Red Pyramid"
msgstr "QΡ±rmΡ±zΡ± ehram"

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board6.qml:51
msgctxt "board6|"
msgid ""
"The Red Pyramid was one of the finest and most successful attempts by "
"Pharaoh Sneferu in building worldβÄôs first ever smooth sided pyramid during "
"the Ancient Egypt period. The height of the pyramid is 104 meters making it "
"the worldβÄôs 4th largest pyramid in Egypt. The pyramid has been built with "
"red limestone stones, hence the name. The local people of Egypt called it as "
"el-heram el-watwaat meaning the Bat Pyramid."
msgstr ""
"QΡ±rmΡ±zΡ± ehram, firon Snofru' nun ilk d…ôf…ô hamar k…ônarlΡ± piramida tikm…ôsin…ô "
"uΡüurlu c…ôhdidir. ehramΡ±n hΟΦndΟΦrlΟΦyΟΦ 104 metrdir, bu da Misird…ô hΟΦndΟΦrlΟΦyΟΦn…ô "
"gΟΕr…ô dΟΕrdΟΦncΟΦ ehramdΡ±r. EhramΡ±n tikintisind…ô tikinti materialΡ± kimi qΡ±rmΡ±zΡ± "
"kir…ôc da≈üΡ±ndan istifad…ô olunmu≈üdur."

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board6.qml:63
msgctxt "board6|"
msgid "Egyptian pyramids"
msgstr "Misir ehramlarΡ±"

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board6.qml:66
msgctxt "board6|"
msgid "Click on the location of the given pyramid."
msgstr "Verilmi≈ü ehramΡ±n yerl…ô≈üdiyi yer…ô vurun."

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board7.qml:17
#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board7.qml:20
msgctxt "board7|"
msgid "Forbidden City"
msgstr ""

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board7.qml:18
msgctxt "board7|"
msgid ""
"The Forbidden City, located in the heart of Beijing, China, is a magnificent "
"imperial palace complex that served as the home of Chinese emperors and the "
"political center of the nation for nearly 500 years, from the Ming dynasty "
"(1368βÄ™1644) to the end of the Qing dynasty (1644βÄ™1912). Built between 1406 "
"and 1420, this sprawling architectural masterpiece spans 180 acres and "
"features over 980 preserved buildings with 8,700 rooms, showcasing "
"traditional Chinese palatial design. Surrounded by a moat and a massive "
"wall, the Forbidden City was once inaccessible to the general public, "
"symbolizing imperial power and exclusivity."
msgstr ""

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board7.qml:28
#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board7.qml:31
msgctxt "board7|"
msgid "Leshan Giant Buddha"
msgstr ""

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board7.qml:29
msgctxt "board7|"
msgid ""
"The Leshan Giant Buddha, located in Sichuan Province, China, is a colossal "
"statue carved into a cliff at the confluence of the Min, Dadu, and Qingyi "
"rivers. Standing at 71 meters (233 feet), it is the tallest pre-modern "
"statue in the world and a UNESCO World Heritage Site. Built during the Tang "
"Dynasty (713βÄ™803 AD), the statue represents Maitreya, the Buddha of the "
"future, and was created to calm the turbulent waters threatening local boat "
"traffic. Ingeniously designed, the statue includes a hidden drainage system "
"to prevent erosion. Its serene expression and intricate craftsmanship make "
"it a symbol of spiritual and artistic achievement."
msgstr ""

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board7.qml:39
#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board7.qml:42
#, fuzzy
#| msgctxt "board2|"
#| msgid "Mysore Palace"
msgctxt "board7|"
msgid "Potala Palace"
msgstr "Maysur SarayΡ±"

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board7.qml:40
msgctxt "board7|"
msgid ""
"The Potala Palace, perched on Red Hill in Lhasa, Tibet, is an iconic symbol "
"of Tibetan culture and a UNESCO World Heritage Site. Originally built in the "
"7th century and expanded in the 17th century, it served as the winter "
"residence of the Dalai Lamas and the center of Tibetan governance. Rising 13 "
"stories high with over 1,000 rooms, the palace combines intricate Tibetan "
"architecture, vibrant murals, and sacred relics. It is divided into the "
"White Palace, housing administrative areas, and the Red Palace, dedicated to "
"religious studies and prayer. The Potala Palace stands as a testament to "
"Tibet's spiritual and historical legacy."
msgstr ""

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board7.qml:50
#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board7.qml:53
msgctxt "board7|"
msgid "Terracotta Army"
msgstr ""

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board7.qml:51
msgctxt "board7|"
msgid ""
"The Terracotta Army is a collection of thousands of life-sized clay "
"soldiers, horses, and chariots buried with China's first emperor, Qin Shi "
"Huang, to accompany him in the afterlife. Discovered in 1974 near Xi'an, the "
"figures date back to approximately 210 BCE and are celebrated for their "
"incredible detail, with each warrior uniquely crafted to represent the "
"diverse ranks and roles of an ancient Chinese army."
msgstr ""

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board7.qml:61
#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board7.qml:64
msgctxt "board7|"
msgid "Sun and Moon Pagodas"
msgstr ""

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board7.qml:62
msgctxt "board7|"
msgid ""
"The Sun and Moon Pagodas, located in Guilin, China, are iconic twin towers "
"that symbolize the city's cultural and spiritual heritage. Originally built "
"during the Tang Dynasty, they were reconstructed in the 20th century as "
"striking landmarks on Shanhu Lake. The Sun Pagoda, standing 41 meters tall, "
"is a bronze structureβÄîthe tallest of its kind in the worldβÄîwhile the Moon "
"Pagoda, at 35 meters, is built of glazed tiles. These pagodas represent the "
"harmony of yin and yang and are connected by an underwater glass tunnel. "
"Illuminated at night, they are popular attractions showcasing traditional "
"Chinese architecture and modern ingenuity."
msgstr ""

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board7.qml:72
#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board7.qml:75
#, fuzzy
#| msgctxt "board3|"
#| msgid "Eiffel Tower"
msgctxt "board7|"
msgid "Diaolou Towers"
msgstr "Eyfel ΟΦll…ôsi"

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board7.qml:73
msgctxt "board7|"
msgid ""
"The Diaolou Towers, found in Kaiping, Guangdong Province, China, are "
"fortified multi-story structures built from the late 19th to early 20th "
"centuries to protect against bandits and floods. Blending Western "
"architectural styles like Romanesque and Baroque with traditional Chinese "
"elements, they reflect the wealth and influence of overseas Chinese "
"emigrants. Constructed with reinforced concrete, these towers symbolize a "
"period of cultural and economic transition in rural China. Designated a "
"UNESCO World Heritage Site in 2007, around 1,800 of the original 3,000 "
"towers remain, offering insight into this unique architectural heritage."
msgstr ""

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board7.qml:85
#, fuzzy
#| msgctxt "board2|"
#| msgid "Monuments of India"
msgctxt "board7|"
msgid "Monuments of China"
msgstr "Hindistan abid…ôl…ôri"

#: activities/explore_monuments/resource/board/board7.qml:88
#, fuzzy
