msgstr "Sad…ô …ôd…ôdl…ôri ΟΕyr…ônin."

#. Help manual
#: activities/gnumch-primes/ActivityInfo.qml:23
msgctxt "ActivityInfo|"
msgid ""
"Prime numbers are numbers that are only divisible by themselves and 1. For "
"example, 3 is a prime number, but 4 isn't (because 4 is divisible by 2). You "
"can think of prime numbers as very small families: they only ever have two "
"people in them! Only themselves and 1. You can't fit any other numbers into "
"them with nothing left over. 5 is one of these lonely numbers (only 5 Ο½ 1 = "
"5), but you can see that 6 has 2 and 3 in its family as well (6 Ο½ 1 = 6, 2 Ο½ "
"3 = 6). So 6 is not a prime number."
msgstr ""
"Sad…ô …ôd…ôdl…ôr, yalnΡ±z ΟΕzΟΦn…ô v…ô 1-…ô bΟΕlΟΦnΟΦr. M…ôs…ôl…ôn 3 sad…ô …ôd…ôddir, 4 is…ô "
"deyil (ΟßΟΦnki 4 ΟΕzΟΦnd…ôn v…ô 1-d…ôn ba≈üqa h…ômΟßinin 2-y…ô bΟΕlΟΦnΟΦr). Sad…ô …ôd…ôdl…ôr "
"yalnΡ±z iki n…ôf…ôrd…ôn (ΟΕzΟΦ v…ô 1) ibar…ôt kiΟßik ail…ô kimidir. Ba≈üqa heΟß bir …ôd…ôd "
"uyΡüun g…ôlmir, ΟßΟΦnki bΟΕlΟΦnm…ô n…ôtic…ôsind…ô qalΡ±q qalΡ±r. 5 sad…ô …ôd…ôdl…ôrd…ôn "
"biridir, onu yalnΡ±z 1-…ô vurmaqla 5 almaq olar. 6 ail…ôsind…ô is…ô 2 v…ô 3 var "
"(6Ο½ 1 = 6, 2Ο½ 3 =6). Bu s…ôb…ôbd…ôn 6 sad…ô …ôd…ôd sayΡ±lmΡ±r."

