"ΟΦsuludur."

#: activities/morse_code/FirstScreen.qml:66
msgctxt "FirstScreen|"
msgid ""
"Each Morse code symbol represents either a text character (letter or "
"numeral) or a prosign and is represented by a unique sequence of dots and "
"dashes. The duration of a dash is three times the duration of a dot. To "
"increase the speed of the communication, the code was designed so that the "
"most common letters have the shorter sequences of dots and dashes.\n"
"For example, the most common letter in English, the letter \"E\", has the "
"shortest code, a single dot."
msgstr ""
"H…ôr bir Morze kodu simvolu, ya m…ôtn simvolunu (h…ôrf v…ô ya r…ôq…ôm) v…ô ya durΡüu "
"i≈üar…ôsini t…ômsil edir v…ô unikal nΟΕqt…ô v…ô tire ardΡ±cΡ±llΡ±ΡüΡ± il…ô t…ômsil olunur. "
"Bir tirenin mΟΦdd…ôti bir nΟΕqt…ônin mΟΦdd…ôtind…ôn ΟΦΟß d…ôf…ô Οßoxdur. Τèlaq…ônin "
"sΟΦr…ôtini artΡ±rmaq ΟΦΟßΟΦn kod el…ô t…ô≈ükil olunmu≈üdur ki, …ôn Οßox istifad…ô olunan "
"h…ôrfl…ôr qΡ±sa nΟΕqt…ô il…ô verilsin. M…ôs…ôl…ôn, ingilis dilind…ô …ôn Οßox yayΡ±lmΡ±≈ü "
"h…ôrf olan \"E\" h…ôrfinin …ôn qΡ±sa kod il…ô, t…ôk nΟΕqt…ô il…ô t…ôyin olunur."

