"It is not possible to consume more electricity than what is produced. There "
"is a key limitation in the distribution of electricity, with minor "
"exceptions, electrical energy cannot be stored, and therefore it must be "
"generated as it is needed. A sophisticated system of control is therefore "
"required to ensure electric generation very closely matches the demand. If "
"supply and demand are not in balance, generation plants and transmission "
"equipment can shut down which, in the worst cases, can lead to a major "
"regional blackout."
msgstr ""
"ΡΑstehsal olunandan Οßox elektrik enerjisi istifad…ô etm…ôk olmaz. Bu enerjinin "
"paylanmasΡ±nda …ôsas m…ôhdudiyy…ôtdir. Nadir hallar istisna olmaqla elektrik "
"enerjisinin toplana bilm…ôz v…ô o yalnΡ±z lazΡ±m olduΡüu q…ôd…ôr istehsal "
"olunmalΡ±dΡ±r. ΡΑstehlak olunan elektrik enerjisini onu yΟΦkl…ônm…ôsin…ô "
"uyΡüunla≈üdlrmaq ΟΦΟßΟΦn mΟΦr…ôkk…ôb idar…ôetm…ô sistemi qurulmalΡ±dΡ±r. ΡΑstehsal v…ô "
"istehlak arasΡ±nda tarazlΡ±ΡüΡ±n pozulmasΡ± elektrik stansiyasΡ±nΡ±n i≈üinin "
"dayanmasΡ±na v…ô elektrik ΟΕtΟΦrΟΦcΟΦ x…ôttl…ôrinin i≈üind…ô qΡ±rΡ±lmalara s…ôb…ôb ola "
"bil…ôr. Bu ΟΕz npvb…ôsind…ô elektrik enerjisinin qlobal miqyasda k…ôsilm…ôsin…ô "
"g…ôtirib ΟßΡ±xarar."

